    <item>
      <title>Gaps between layout components in Android</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/2020/05/04/gaps-between-layout-components-in-android/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 04 May 2020 16:27:17 +0000</pubDate>
       <guid isPermaLink="false">http://georgimirchev.com/?p=206</guid> 
      <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a very simple solution in Android if you want to have space between components. You can always set margins but you can also use the &lt;a href=&#34;https://web.archive.org/web/20190722235855/https://developer.android.com/reference/android/widget/Space.html&#34;&gt;Space&lt;/a&gt; class. You can use it like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;lt;Space
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  android:layout_width=&amp;#34;1dp&amp;#34;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  android:layout_height=&amp;#34;30dp&amp;#34;/&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
